        <h2>1. Stewardship - Practice Responsible Stewardship</h2>
        <p align="right" style="font-size:10px"><a href="#top" style="color:black">Back to Top</a></p>
        <h3>Intention</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>We value stewardship and fiscal accountability and always strive to do more with less.  We guard and conserve company resources as if they were our own because it makes good business sense at all times; not just during lean times.</li>
            <li>We invest in areas which will contribute to the long-term sustainability of our company.</li>
            <li>We are focused and serious about the operations of our business.  We believe in working hard and putting in the extra effort to get things done.  In order to stay ahead of the competition, we continuously innovate as well as make incremental improvements to our operations, always striving to make ourselves more efficient and finding ways to do things better</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Visioning</h3>
        <p>
            <button data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#demo">Read the story behind stewardship</button>

            <div id="demo" class="collapse">
                As the leaders of the company sat down to sketch out the 5 year strategic growth plan for the organization, they carefully evaluated projected cash flow and reserves.  Given the economic challenges, it was decided to postpone the opening of a new office in North Carolina for a year.  Since they had a highly qualified individual selected to launch that office, Andrea, they brought her into the organization to take on an interim role until the economic conditions turned around and the company could comfortably invest and move forward.
                Andrea approached her interim work with enthusiasm and made all of her decisions as if she were a partner in the company.  She booked all of her travel using an aggregator site to find the very best pricing on airfare, rental cars and hotels.  She was able to stay at quality hotels for a fraction of the cost of the discount chains.  She always asked herself if it was her checkbook, was she getting the most for her money.  Andrea’s example led others on her team to follow suit and find restaurants that exceeded expectations on quality and were easy on the wallet.
                Andrea’s interim project was unexpectedly targeted as part of the client’s mid-year budget cutting exercise.  Two of her teammates ended up back on the Centric bench.  While new roles were being identified, they both took on internal initiatives which were challenging and needed to support recent growth of the company.  They learned firsthand that leveraging consultants on the bench who are between billable roles has enabled Centric to limit the overhead associated with back office operations while continuing to expand the organization and improve the efficiency.
                Andrea was able to directly contribute to the vision of turning Centric into a 100 year sustainable for many generations to come company through her daily actions which exemplified the core values.
            </div>
            
        </p>
