        <h2>3. Innovation - Strive to Innovate</h2>
        <p align="right" style="font-size:10px"><a href="#top" style="color:black">Back to Top</a></p>
        <h3>Intention</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>We constantly seek to foster an entrepreneurial, hard-working, fun loving culture that encourages innovation and prudent individual or team risk taking within the context of our core values.</li>
            <li>Centric values passion, determination, perseverance, and innovation.   We are inspired because we believe in what we are doing and where we are going.  We believe in using innovation to remove obstacles and help our clients succeed in their goals.</li>
            <li>We value courageous, unconventional thinking and strive to bring an optimistic attitude to all that we do because we realize that this inspires others to have the same attitude.</li>
            
        </ul>
        <h3>Visioning</h3>
        <p>
            <button data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#demo3">Read the story behind innovation</button>

            <div id="demo3" class="collapse">
                Fahim was working with his client, Metropolis Industries, to come up with a solution that would increase the efficiency of their robotic assembly line.  The existing process required oversight by plant personnel while the line was running to minimize down-time when assembly of a particular component failed.  If they could come up with an automated way to monitor the activity and alert the on-call employees when a problem occurred, they could reallocate those staff members to other areas of the plant operations.  The stumbling block was that the manufacturer of the automated system would not allow modifications to the software or hardware that controlled the mechanisms.

                After another frustrating day of unsuccessful brainstorming with the R&D team, Fahim headed out to mow his lawn and half-way through an idea began to form.  What if they could develop an external mechanism that could be strategically placed along the assembly line to monitor activity and if it detected a change in the normal flow, would immediately send alerts via mobile phone and email to the on-call team?  This would get around the constraint of the manufacturer and provide an alternative solution.  He thought about it some more as he finished his lawn and headed inside to put together his idea to present the next day to his Centric colleagues to develop further.

                Fahim worked with the Centric Innovation and Research group to develop a design behind his idea.  They built several prototypes before finding the winning formula which tested out and was ready to be presented to the client for consideration.  The time Centric invested in thinking through and developing a working prototype was invaluable for the experience and synergies gained among the technology team members and the lessons learned were energizing to all.

                Barbara and Randy, the Senior Executives at Metropolis who had been working on this problem, were thrilled with Fahim’s idea and the prototype that Centric developed.  They immediately called together the R&D team to work with Fahim to test and refine the product in their environment.  Three weeks later, they were able to successfully implement the solution and reallocate some staff members to other critical areas in the plant that needed attention.

                The perseverance Fahim and the Centric team displayed and the willingness to take a risk had paid off.  They felt a great sense of accomplishment which was externally reinforced when they and the lead R&D researchers from Metropolis were recognized with the Innovator of the Year award.

                Innovation coupled with determination, prudent risk taking and the courage to pursue new ideas is a cornerstone of Centric’s success!
            </div>
        
        </p>
    </div>

